reviewText:
The good:

-Atmosphere;
-Trading cards.

The bad:

-I finished the game (and I explorered a bit) in 30 minutes (I wasted more time waiting for the cards than finish the actual game;
-The cursor disappears when you try to change audio settings;
-Unpolished game (I play MGSV: TPP with solid 30 fps yet this unity engine created game I run at low settings and I have a 13 FPS drops);
-Not worth the 2€.

Score: 3/10

What can i say... this game is impossible to play...

- no information what you pick;
- game settings are not being saved;
- you can't SAVE?!?
- pressing ESC closes the game without even asking if you are sure;
- when you run out of batteries you cant proceed...
- even on medium this game has awful fps drop, i can barely play it...

i only bought it because of the trading cards...
